This paper focuses on the development of a learning algorithm for dynamic object handover between robots and humans, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of contextual policy search and learning from human feedback suggests a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential for incorporating computer vision (cs.CV) to enable the robot to adapt to object characteristics. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for learning the latent reward function suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
